    {
        "content": "<p>I'm on <a href=\"https://adam.math.hhu.de/#/g/leanprover-community/nng4/world/LessOrEqual/level/5\">level 5 of the &lt;= world</a>. </p>\n<p>This is what I got so far:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hd</span>\n<span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">add_zero</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hd</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hd</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hd</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">nth_rewrite</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">add_left_cancel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add_zero</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_add</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This gives me a goal: <code>0 = succ a</code></p>\n<p>I was hoping to now use <code>zero_ne_succ</code> (which says <code>0 = succ a =&gt; False</code>) to \"close\" this line of argument. But it doesn't seem like I can <code>apply</code> it:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero_ne_succ</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">tactic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">'</span><span class=\"n\">apply'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unify</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">False</span>\n<span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm guessing I'm coming at it from a wrong angle and I can't use <code>apply</code> for contradictions? Or am I misreading this?</p>",
        "id": 497119248,
        "sender_full_name": "Dan Abramov",
        "timestamp": 1738375752
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If the current goal is <code>0 = succ a</code>, then the goal is not provable. If you have <code>0 = succ a</code> as a hypothesis and the goal is <code>False</code> then you could <code>apply zero_ne_succ</code> to prove <code>False</code>.</p>",
        "id": 497119594,
        "sender_full_name": "Paige Thomas",
        "timestamp": 1738376058
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Your direction is wrong. If a theorem is <code>p -&gt; q</code> and the goal is <code>q</code> then you can use <code>apply</code> to turn your goal into<code>p</code>.</p>",
        "id": 497119621,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhang Qinchuan",
        "timestamp": 1738376082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Got it, makes sense. I guess I was going after a proof by contradiction but <code>apply</code> isn't the right tool for this!</p>\n<p>This is what I ended up with:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hd</span>\n<span class=\"n\">symm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hd</span>\n<span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">add_right_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hd</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(Not sure if there's a more idiomatic way to express this in the game — I kind of guessed the trick with using parens but I don't think it was taught directly...)</p>",
        "id": 497119823,
        "sender_full_name": "Dan Abramov",
        "timestamp": 1738376271
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The parentheses are unneeded, function application associates left by default.<br>\nYou can just write <code>add_right_eq_zero x d hd</code></p>",
        "id": 497120206,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1738376558
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ahh I see.  So in this notation:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">add_right_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">✝</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The parens don't serve a significant role other than to group several things of the same type?</p>\n<p>In other words, is this just a shorter form of</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">add_right_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">✝</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>?</p>",
